The Cape Kidney Association in partnership with the City of Cape Town will host their annual charity sunset 5km walk on Thursday 14 March in commemoration of World Kidney Day. The kidney awareness walk will start at the Mouille Point lighthouse. Registration will commence from 15:00 and the walk will start at 18:00. Entry fee is R60 per person. Children under the age of six enter free. The theme for the 2019 walk is “Kidney health for everyone, everywhere”. For more information, call 021 761 1326.